Date: 1997-09-02

Title: Multiloop $\Phi^3$ Amplitudes from Bosonic String Theory

Comments: 1+26 pages (Latex), 4 figures included (PicTex)

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B515 (1998) 488-508

We show how the multiloop amplitudes of $\Phi^3$ theory (in the worldlineformulation of Schmidt and Schubert) are recovered from the N-tachyon$(h+1)$-loop amplitude in bosonic string theory in the $\alpha' \to 0$ limit,if one keeps the tachyon coupling constant fixed. In this limit the integralover string moduli space receives contributions only from those corners wherethe world-sheet resembles a $\Phi^3$ particle diagram. Technical issuesinvolved are a proper choice of local world-sheet coordinates, needed to takethe string amplitudes off-shell, and a formal procedure for introducing a freemass parameter $M^2$ instead of the tachyonic value $-4/\alpha'$.